{% extends "_base.njk" %}
{% set description = "Voting matters. Organizing matters. This is the plan that gives both something to build toward — from policy platform to structural constitutional reform." %}
{% block title %}The Plan — Freedom and Dignity Project{% endblock %}
{% block og_description %}Voting matters. Organizing matters. This is the plan that gives both something to build toward — from policy platform to structural constitutional reform.{% endblock %}
{% block og_url %}plan.html{% endblock %}
{% block twitter_description %}Voting matters. Organizing matters. This is the plan that gives both something to build toward.{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<header class="page-hero-standard">
  <span class="hero-eyebrow">The Path Forward</span>
  <h1>The <span>Plan</span></h1>
  <p class="hero-statement">Voting matters. Organizing matters. This is the plan that gives both something to build toward.</p>
</header>

<!-- WHY NOTHING ELSE IS ENOUGH -->
<section class="bg-cream ruled" aria-labelledby="why-heading">
<div class="wrap">
  <div class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--mid)">Why Nothing Else Is Enough</div>
  <h2 id="why-heading">Every Platform That's Failed Has the Same Flaw</h2>
  <p>It defines what we want without explaining how we get there. Voting for better candidates is necessary. Legislative pressure is important. Neither is structural. When the rules that govern elections, rights, and accountability are themselves broken, winning inside those rules doesn't fix them.</p>
  <p>The goal of this project is not to win the next election. It's to change what the next election is fought over — and the one after that, and the one after that — until the structural guarantees that make democracy work are built into the foundation and not dependent on who happens to be in power.</p>
  <div class="pullquote">
    Every platform that's failed has the same flaw: it defines what we want without explaining how we get there. This is the how.
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- THE THREE PHASES -->
<section class="bg-dark on-dark ruled" aria-labelledby="phases-heading">
<div class="wrap">
  <div class="eyebrow">The Three Phases</div>
  <h2 id="phases-heading">A Path from Platform to Structural Reform</h2>
  <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.75);max-width:640px;margin-bottom:2rem">Constitutional reform requires a coalition large enough and organized enough to pursue permanent structural change. That coalition doesn't appear fully formed. It gets built, deliberately, over time.</p>

  <div class="policyos-layers">
    <div class="layer-card">
      <div class="layer-card-num">Phase 1</div>
      <div class="layer-card-title">The Foundation</div>
      <div class="layer-card-body">Build the platform. Build the coalition. Establish the demands. The policy library defines exactly what we're fighting for — numbered, traceable, specific enough that any candidate or institution either stands for them or doesn't. The Human Review System (in development) democratizes the platform itself: reviewed, challenged, and strengthened by the people it's meant to serve.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="layer-card">
      <div class="layer-card-num">Phase 2</div>
      <div class="layer-card-title">The Campaign</div>
      <div class="layer-card-body">Apply organized electoral and legislative pressure. Candidates adopt positions from the platform. Incumbents are held to a specific ledger, not vague values. The demands don't shift based on who's running or who's in power. When a coalition of millions organizes around the same concrete demands, institutions have to respond.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="layer-card">
      <div class="layer-card-num">Phase 3</div>
      <div class="layer-card-title">The Transformation</div>
      <div class="layer-card-body">Pursue structural and constitutional reform. Voting rights, anti-corruption, campaign finance, rights guarantees — built into the foundation, not dependent on the next election. This is not a shortcut. It requires a large, durable coalition organized around specific demands. That is exactly what the previous two phases exist to build.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- WHERE WE ARE NOW -->
<section class="bg-parchment ruled" aria-labelledby="now-heading">
<div class="wrap">
  <div class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--mid)">Where We Are Now</div>
  <h2 id="now-heading">We're in Phase 1</h2>
  <div class="arch-intro" style="gap:1.75rem">
    <div class="arch-item">
      <div class="arch-item-label">The Platform Is Live</div>
      <p>The policy library covers <span data-dynamic="pillar-count">26</span> pillars and over <span data-dynamic="policy-count">200</span> individual positions. Each position has a canonical ID, a formal policy statement, a plain-language summary, and a legal basis. The foundation is built. The demands are defined.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-item">
      <div class="arch-item-label">The Human Review System</div>
      <p>The platform is designed to be permanent, not finished. The Human Review System — in development — will allow people to review positions, contribute research, and formally challenge claims. Coalition means intellectual participation, not just political support.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- BRIDGE TO GET INVOLVED -->
<div class="page-nav-cta">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p>The coalition gets built one person at a time. Here's your role in this.</p>
    <a href="get-involved.html" class="btn-primary">Get Involved →</a>
  </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
